        <p>Leo Fender - The creator of the strat</p>
        <h2>About the Stratocaster</h2>
        <p>
            The Fender Stratocaster (often called the "Strat") is one of the most popular and recognizable electric guitars in the world. 
            It is known for its bright, clear tone and comfortable body shape, making it a great choice for beginners and professionals alike.
        </p>

        <h2>History</h2>
        <p>
            The Stratocaster was introduced in 1954 by Fender and designed by Leo Fender. 
            It was one of the first guitars to feature a contoured body for comfort and three single-coil pickups for a wide range of tones. 
            Over time, it became a staple in many genres and is still one of the best-selling guitars ever made.
        </p>
        <img width="250" src="Images/First_strat.jpg" alt="Fender Stratocaster Electric Guitar">
        <p>The first stratocaster</p>

        <h2>Common Uses</h2>
        <p>The Fender Stratocaster is especially known for:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Clean tones in pop, funk, and country music</li>
            <li>Blues and expressive lead playing</li>
            <li>Classic rock rhythm and solos</li>
            <li>Versatile sound for many genres</li>
            <li>Comfortable playing for beginners</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Famous Players</h2>
        <p>
            Many legendary guitarists have used the Stratocaster, including Jimi Hendrix, Eric Clapton, and John Mayer.
        </p>

